I’m usually pretty chipper about WOTC decision-making but I am a little jaded this morning. I know we have to pay our dues before we get great previews, but giving Maro two previews, one of which is a great EDH powerhouse that he offhandedly spoils without much detail in his article today, is a little annoying when EDHREC, the most popular site for this format, is getting middling uncommons that probably won’t see play except in niche decks. It’s not intentionally malicious, but it’s not a good feel. Content creators usually get cards befitting their content, and it’s not exactly a mystery what we’re about. 

Anyway, enough complaining, but I just had to get that out of my brain. A little bitter, this feels tone deaf and that’s not a good start to my morning.
